## Editing a Published Playbook

To edit an active playbook, open the playbook from the list, click **Edit** in the top-right header, and then make your changes. Changes are saved as a new draft and do not affect the currently active published version until you publish again.

<Frame>
  <img src="/images/graphium/playbooks/edit-playbook.png" alt="Edit button in the playbook editor header" />
</Frame>

---

## Disabling a Playbook

To stop a playbook from running, disable it. A disabled playbook will not fire on schedule, cannot be triggered manually, and will not respond to connection or vault events until re-enabled. For connection-triggered playbooks, disabling also pauses the deployed trigger on the external service.

